  "read": "TileLang score-page sparse-MLA backward pipeline gate. It uses the same real q/dO/output/lse plus compressed KV source boundary as recompute_pdp_store_then_dkv_limited, but runs producer and selected-limit final-dKV consumer one token page at a time. Each page materializes a smaller BF16 P/scaled-dP score page, consumes it immediately into a page-local final dKV tensor, then adds that page contribution into the returned [groups, D] output. This is an HBM/L2 score-page upper bound for the desired on-chip producer/consumer ring buffer; it does not yet provide cross-CTA LDS sharing. This run feeds real TorchTitan sparse-MLA boundary tensors into the TileLang dKV producer. Materialized per-head probs and scaled grad_logits are present only for materialized-input modes or correctness-reference checks; recompute mode uses q/dO/output/lse/compressed KV in the timed producer.",
